The paper discusses the use of deep learning for creating and detecting deceptive explanations, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The empirical evaluation focuses on text classification, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The topic of deception and detection also relates to computer security (cs.CR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC), which are additional possible sub-categories.
